      "writtenOn": "2017-02-10T01:26:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Here’s a thing that you can do with argparse that lets it do this stuff for you:\n\nparser.add_argument(\u0027defs\u0027)  # you can also provide help\u003d or anything else you like\nparser.add_argument(\u0027user_c\u0027)\nparser.add_argument(\u0027server_c\u0027)\nparser.add_argument(\u0027user_h\u0027)\nparser.add_argument(\u0027server_h\u0027)\n\nIt calls these “positional” arguments and demands that they show up in the argument list. That lets you do parsed \u003d parser.parse_args() (instead of parse_known_args()), and it gets rid of the assert len(unknown_args) \u003d\u003d 5 and this line, and lets you address the positional arguments as parsed.defs, parsed.user_c, etc.",
      "revId": "46079e9f7eed622b41d38dfff3ca533ecbe777d0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
